VLSM Message Properties

Section equivocator_vlsm_message_properties.

Lifting properties about sent messages to the equivocators

In this section we first prove some general properties about sent messages being preserved and reflected by the equivocator_vlsm, and then we show that the HasBeenSentCapability and the ComputableSentMessages can be lifted (each separately) from the original machine to the equivocator_vlsm. 
Context
  {message : Type}
  (X : VLSM message)
  (equivocator_vlsm := equivocator_vlsm X)
  (MachineDescriptor := MachineDescriptor X)
  .
If a projection of an equivocator_vlsm trace outputs a message, then the original trace must do so too. 
message: Type
X: VLSM message
equivocator_vlsm:= Common.equivocator_vlsm X: VLSM message
MachineDescriptor:= Common.MachineDescriptor X: Type
tr: list (vtransition_item equivocator_vlsm)
trX: list (vtransition_item X)
j, i: MachineDescriptor
HtrX: equivocator_vlsm_trace_project X tr j =
Some (trX, i)
m: message
Hjbs: Exists (field_selector output m) trX
Exists (field_selector output m) tr

IHtr: ‚àÄ (trX : list (vtransition_item X)) 
  (i : MachineDescriptor),
  equivocator_vlsm_trace_project X tr j =
  Some (trX, i)
  ‚Üí Exists (field_selector output m) trX
    ‚Üí Exists (field_selector output m) tr
trX: list (vtransition_item X)
i: MachineDescriptor
HtrX: match
  equivocator_vlsm_trace_project X tr j
with
| Some (r, idescriptor) =>
    match
      equivocator_vlsm_transition_item_project
        X a idescriptor
    with
    | Some (Some item', odescriptor) =>
        Some (item' :: r, odescriptor)
    | Some (None, odescriptor) =>
        Some (r, odescriptor)
    | None => None
    end
| None => None
end = Some (trX, i)
Hjbs: Exists (field_selector output m) trX
Exists (field_selector output m) (a :: tr)

message: Type
X: VLSM message
equivocator_vlsm:= Common.equivocator_vlsm X: VLSM message
MachineDescriptor:= Common.MachineDescriptor X: Type
bs: vstate equivocator_vlsm
btr: list (vtransition_item equivocator_vlsm)
Hbtr: finite_valid_trace_from
  (pre_loaded_with_all_messages_vlsm
     equivocator_vlsm) bs btr
bitem: vtransition_item equivocator_vlsm
Hitem: bitem ‚àà btr
sn: state
Hnew: l bitem = Spawn sn
input bitem = None
‚àß output bitem = None

MachineDescriptor:= Common.MachineDescriptor X: Type
bs, bf: vstate equivocator_vlsm
bprefix, bsuffix: list (vtransition_item equivocator_vlsm)
lst: state
Heqlst: lst = finite_trace_last bs bprefix
Hbprefix: finite_valid_trace_from_to
  (pre_loaded_with_all_messages_vlsm
     equivocator_vlsm) bs lst bprefix
s: state
iom, oom: option message
l: label
Hbsuffix: finite_valid_trace_from_to
  (pre_loaded_with_all_messages_vlsm
     equivocator_vlsm) lst bf
  ({|
     l := l;
     input := iom;
     destination := s;
     output := oom
   |} :: bsuffix)
idl: nat
Hinv2: ‚àÄ (j : nat) (di : Common.MachineDescriptor X) 
  (trX : list (vtransition_item X)),
  equivocator_vlsm_trace_project X
    (bprefix ++
     {|
       l := l;
       input := iom;
       destination := s;
       output := oom
     |} :: bsuffix) (Existing j) =
  Some (trX, di)
  ‚Üí ‚àÉ fsj : vstate X,
      equivocator_state_project bf j =
      Some fsj
      ‚àß match di with
        | NewMachine sn =>
            finite_valid_trace_init_to
              (pre_loaded_with_all_messages_vlsm
                 X) sn fsj trX
        | Existing i =>
            ‚àÉ isi : vstate X,
              equivocator_state_project bs i =
              Some isi
              ‚àß finite_valid_trace_from_to
                  (pre_loaded_with_all_messages_vlsm
                     X) isi fsj trX
                ‚àß (vinitial_state_prop
                     (pre_loaded_with_all_messages_vlsm
                      (Common.equivocator_vlsm
                      X)) bs
                   ‚Üí vinitial_state_prop
                      (pre_loaded_with_all_messages_vlsm
                      X) isi)
        end
Hlbitem: equivocator_label_descriptor l =
Existing idl
Htl: finite_valid_trace_from
  (pre_loaded_with_all_messages_vlsm
     equivocator_vlsm) s bsuffix
Hv: valid l (lst, iom)
Ht: transition l (lst, iom) = (s, oom)
Hpitem: ‚àÄ _i : nat,
  equivocator_label_descriptor l =
  Existing _i
  ‚Üí ‚àÉ (i : nat) (si : vstate X),
      equivocator_state_project s i = Some si
      ‚àß (‚àÉ itemx : vtransition_item X,
           equivocator_vlsm_transition_item_project
             X
             {|
               l := l;
               input := iom;
               destination := s;
               output := oom
             |} (Existing i) =
           Some (Some itemx, Existing _i))
i: nat
si: vstate X
Hi: equivocator_state_project s i = Some si
itemx: vtransition_item X
dsuffix: Common.MachineDescriptor X
Heqdsuffix: dsuffix = Existing i
Hitemx: equivocator_vlsm_transition_item_project X
  {|
    l := l;
    input := iom;
    destination := s;
    output := oom
  |} dsuffix =
Some (Some itemx, Existing idl)
suffix: list (vtransition_item X)
Hsuffix: equivocator_vlsm_trace_project X bsuffix
  dsuffix = Some (suffix, dsuffix)
‚àÉ tr : list (vtransition_item X),
  itemx ‚àà tr
  ‚àß (‚àÉ dfinal dfirst : MachineDescriptor,
       proper_descriptor X dfirst bs
       ‚àß existing_descriptor X dfinal
           (finite_trace_last bs
              (bprefix ++

bs, bf: vstate equivocator_vlsm
bprefix, bsuffix: list (vtransition_item equivocator_vlsm)
lst: state
Heqlst: lst = finite_trace_last bs bprefix
Hbprefix: finite_valid_trace_from_to
  (pre_loaded_with_all_messages_vlsm
     equivocator_vlsm) bs lst bprefix
s: state
iom, oom: option message
l: label
Hbsuffix: finite_valid_trace_from_to
  (pre_loaded_with_all_messages_vlsm
     equivocator_vlsm) lst bf
  ({|
     l := l;
     input := iom;
     destination := s;
     output := oom
   |} :: bsuffix)
idl: nat
Hinv2: ‚àÄ (j : nat) (di : Common.MachineDescriptor X) 
  (trX : list (vtransition_item X)),
  equivocator_vlsm_trace_project X
    (bprefix ++
     {|
       l := l;
       input := iom;
       destination := s;
       output := oom
     |} :: bsuffix) (Existing j) =
  Some (trX, di)
  ‚Üí ‚àÉ fsj : vstate X,
      equivocator_state_project bf j =
      Some fsj
      ‚àß match di with
        | NewMachine sn =>
            finite_valid_trace_init_to
              (pre_loaded_with_all_messages_vlsm
                 X) sn fsj trX
        | Existing i =>
            ‚àÉ isi : vstate X,
              equivocator_state_project bs i =
              Some isi
              ‚àß finite_valid_trace_from_to
                  (pre_loaded_with_all_messages_vlsm
                     X) isi fsj trX
                ‚àß (vinitial_state_prop
                     (pre_loaded_with_all_messages_vlsm
                      (Common.equivocator_vlsm
                      X)) bs
                   ‚Üí vinitial_state_prop
                      (pre_loaded_with_all_messages_vlsm
                      X) isi)
        end
Hlbitem: equivocator_label_descriptor l =
Existing idl
Htl: finite_valid_trace_from
  (pre_loaded_with_all_messages_vlsm
     equivocator_vlsm) s bsuffix
Hv: valid l (lst, iom)
Ht: transition l (lst, iom) = (s, oom)
Hpitem: ‚àÄ _i : nat,
  equivocator_label_descriptor l =
  Existing _i
  ‚Üí ‚àÉ (i : nat) (si : vstate X),
      equivocator_state_project s i = Some si
      ‚àß (‚àÉ itemx : vtransition_item X,
           equivocator_vlsm_transition_item_project
             X
             {|
               l := l;
               input := iom;
               destination := s;
               output := oom
             |} (Existing i) =
           Some (Some itemx, Existing _i))
i: nat
si: vstate X
Hi: equivocator_state_project s i = Some si
itemx: vtransition_item X
Hitemx: equivocator_vlsm_transition_item_project X
  {|
    l := l;
    input := iom;
    destination := s;
    output := oom
  |} (Existing i) =
Some (Some itemx, Existing idl)
suffix: list (vtransition_item X)
Hsuffix: equivocator_vlsm_trace_project X bsuffix
  (Existing i) = Some (suffix, Existing i)
Hsuffix': equivocator_vlsm_trace_project X
  ([{|
      l := l;
      input := iom;
      destination := s;
      output := oom
    |}] ++ bsuffix) (Existing i) =
Some ([itemx] ++ suffix, Existing idl)
_i: nat
_Hdsuffix: Existing i = Existing _i
s_i: vstate X
_Hi: equivocator_state_project s _i = Some s_i
Hd': ‚àÉ i' : nat,
  Existing idl = Existing i'
  ‚àß (‚àÉ s'x : vstate X,
       equivocator_state_project lst i' =
       Some s'x
       ‚àß (‚àÉ Hex : existing_equivocator_label X l,
            let lx :=
              existing_equivocator_label_extract
                X l Hex in
            itemx =
            {|
              l := lx;
              input := iom;
              destination := s_i;
              output := oom
            |}
            ‚àß vvalid X lx (s'x, iom)
              ‚àß vtransition X lx (s'x, iom) =
                (s_i, oom)))
H0: i = _i
‚àÉ tr : list (vtransition_item X),
  itemx ‚àà tr
  ‚àß (‚àÉ dfinal dfirst : MachineDescriptor,
       proper_descriptor X dfirst bs
       ‚àß existing_descriptor X dfinal
           (finite_trace_last bs
              (bprefix ++
               {|
                 l := l;
                 input := iom;
                 destination := s;
                 output := oom
               |} :: bsuffix))
         ‚àß equivocator_vlsm_trace_project X
             (bprefix ++
              {|
                l := l;
                input := iom;
                destination := s;
                output := oom
              |} :: bsuffix) dfinal =
           Some (tr, dfirst))

  (pre_loaded_with_all_messages_vlsm
     equivocator_vlsm) bs
  (finite_trace_last bs bprefix) bprefix
s: state
iom, oom: option message
l: label
Hbsuffix: finite_valid_trace_from_to
  (pre_loaded_with_all_messages_vlsm
     equivocator_vlsm)
  (finite_trace_last bs bprefix) bf
  ({|
     l := l;
     input := iom;
     destination := s;
     output := oom
   |} :: bsuffix)
idl, i: nat
itemx: vtransition_item X
suffix, prefix: list (vtransition_item X)
dfirst: Common.MachineDescriptor X
Hlbitem: equivocator_label_descriptor l =
Existing idl
Htl: finite_valid_trace_from
  (pre_loaded_with_all_messages_vlsm
     equivocator_vlsm) s bsuffix
Ht: transition l (finite_trace_last bs bprefix, iom) =
(s, oom)
Hv: valid l (finite_trace_last bs bprefix, iom)
Hpitem: ‚àÄ _i : nat,
  equivocator_label_descriptor l =
  Existing _i
  ‚Üí ‚àÉ (i : nat) (si : vstate X),
      equivocator_state_project s i = Some si
      ‚àß (‚àÉ itemx : vtransition_item X,
           equivocator_vlsm_transition_item_project
             X
             {|
               l := l;
               input := iom;
               destination := s;
               output := oom
             |} (Existing i) =
           Some (Some itemx, Existing _i))
si: vstate X
Hi: equivocator_state_project s i = Some si
Hitemx: equivocator_vlsm_transition_item_project X
  {|
    l := l;
    input := iom;
    destination := s;
    output := oom
  |} (Existing i) =
Some (Some itemx, Existing idl)
Hsuffix: equivocator_vlsm_trace_project X bsuffix
  (Existing i) = Some (suffix, Existing i)
Hsuffix': equivocator_vlsm_trace_project X
  ([{|
      l := l;
      input := iom;
      destination := s;
      output := oom
    |}] ++ bsuffix) (Existing i) =
Some ([itemx] ++ suffix, Existing idl)
s_i: vstate X
_Hi: equivocator_state_project s i = Some s_i
lst_i': vstate X
id: equivocator_state_project
  (finite_trace_last bs bprefix) idl =
Some lst_i'
Hex: existing_equivocator_label X l
_Hitemx: itemx =
{|
  l :=
    existing_equivocator_label_extract X l
      Hex;
  input := iom;
  destination := s_i;
  output := oom
|}
Hvs': vvalid X
  (existing_equivocator_label_extract X l Hex)
  (lst_i', iom)
Hts': vtransition X
  (existing_equivocator_label_extract X l Hex)
  (lst_i', iom) = (s_i, oom)
Hprefix: equivocator_vlsm_trace_project X bprefix
  (Existing idl) = Some (prefix, dfirst)
Htr: equivocator_vlsm_trace_project X
  (bprefix ++
   {|
     l := l;
     input := iom;
     destination := s;
     output := oom
   |} :: bsuffix) (Existing i) =
Some (prefix ++ itemx :: suffix, dfirst)
bfi: vstate X
Hdfinal: equivocator_state_project bf i = Some bfi
Hdinitial: match dfirst with
| NewMachine sn =>
    finite_valid_trace_init_to
      (pre_loaded_with_all_messages_vlsm X)
      sn bfi (prefix ++ itemx :: suffix)
| Existing i =>
    ‚àÉ isi : vstate X,
      equivocator_state_project bs i =
      Some isi
      ‚àß finite_valid_trace_from_to
          (pre_loaded_with_all_messages_vlsm
             X) isi bfi
          (prefix ++ itemx :: suffix)
        ‚àß (vinitial_state_prop
             (pre_loaded_with_all_messages_vlsm
                (Common.equivocator_vlsm X))
             bs
           ‚Üí vinitial_state_prop
               (pre_loaded_with_all_messages_vlsm
                  X) isi)

Qed.
If an equivocator_vlsm's valid trace segment outputs a message, then one of its projections must do so too.

     equivocator_vlsm) is tr
m: message
Hbbs: Exists (field_selector output m) tr
‚àÉ (j i : MachineDescriptor) (_ : proper_descriptor X i
                                   is) (_ : existing_descriptor
                                              X j
                                              (finite_trace_last
                                                 is tr)) 
  (trX : list (vtransition_item X)) (_ : equivocator_vlsm_trace_project
                                           X tr j =
                                         Some (trX, i)),
  Exists (field_selector output m) trX

Section oracle_lifting.

Context
  selector
  (Hselector_io : forall l1 l2 s1 s2 im om m, selector m  {| l:= l1; input := im; destination := s1; output := om |} <-> selector m  {| l:= l2; input := im; destination := s2; output := om |})
  oracle
  (Hdec : RelDecision oracle)
  (Hstepwise : oracle_stepwise_props (vlsm := X) selector oracle).

Definition equivocator_selector
  (m : message)
  (item : vtransition_item equivocator_vlsm)
  : Prop
  :=
  match (l item) with
  | Spawn _ => False
  | ContinueWith _ l | ForkWith _ l =>
    selector m
      {| l := l
       ; input := input item
       ; destination := equivocator_state_zero (destination item)
       ; output := output item
      |}
  end.
We define equivocator_oracle for the equivocator_vlsm as being the oracle for any of the internal machines. 
Definition equivocator_oracle
  (s : vstate equivocator_vlsm)
  (m : message)
  : Prop
  :=
  exists i si, equivocator_state_project s i = Some si /\
    oracle si m.

X: VLSM message

selector: message ‚Üí transition_item ‚Üí Prop
Hselector_io: ‚àÄ (l1 l2 : label) (s1 s2 : state) 
  (im om : option message) 
  (m : message),
  selector m
    {|
      l := l1;
      input := im;
      destination := s1;
      output := om
    |}
  ‚Üî selector m
      {|
        l := l2;
        input := im;
        destination := s2;
        output := om
      |}
oracle: vstate X ‚Üí message ‚Üí Prop
Hdec: RelDecision oracle
Hstepwise: oracle_stepwise_props selector oracle
RelDecision equivocator_oracle

m: message
i: nat

Decision (oracle v m)
 apply Hdec.

Hstepwise: oracle_stepwise_props selector oracle
oracle_no_inits: ‚àÄ s : vstate X,
  initial_state_prop s
  ‚Üí ‚àÄ m : message, ¬¨ oracle s m
oracle_step_update: ‚àÄ (l : label) (s : state) 
  (im : option message) 
  (s' : state) (om : option
                      message),
  input_valid_transition
    (pre_loaded_with_all_messages_vlsm
       X) l (s, im) (s', om)
  ‚Üí ‚àÄ msg : message,
      oracle s' msg
      ‚Üî selector msg
          {|
            l := l;
            input := im;
            destination := s';
            output := om
          |} ‚à® oracle s msg
sdesc: vstate X
s: state
Hs: valid_state_prop
  (pre_loaded_with_all_messages_vlsm
     equivocator_vlsm) s
Hisdesc: vinitial_state_prop X sdesc
msg: message
ins: nat
sins: vstate X
Hsins: equivocator_state_project s ins = Some sins
Hir: oracle sins msg
‚àÉ (i : nat) (si : vstate X),
  equivocator_state_project
    (equivocator_state_extend s sdesc) i = Some si
  ‚àß oracle si msg

        
message: Type
X: VLSM message
equivocator_vlsm:= Common.equivocator_vlsm X: VLSM message
MachineDescriptor:= Common.MachineDescriptor X: Type
selector: message ‚Üí transition_item ‚Üí Prop
Hselector_io: ‚àÄ (l1 l2 : label) (s1 s2 : state) 
  (im om : option message) 
  (m : message),
  selector m
    {|
      l := l1;
      input := im;
      destination := s1;
      output := om
    |}
  ‚Üî selector m
      {|
        l := l2;
        input := im;
        destination := s2;
        output := om
      |}

  (pre_loaded_with_all_messages_vlsm
     equivocator_vlsm) s

| Some si => vvalid X l (si, im)
| None => False
end
Ht: transition (ContinueWith idesc l) (s, im) =
(s', om)

Heq_im: match
  VLSM.l
    {|
      l := ContinueWith idesc l;
      input := im;
      destination := s';
      output := om
    |}
with
| Spawn _ => False
| ContinueWith _ l0 | ForkWith _ l0 =>
    selector msg
      {|
        l := l0;
        input :=
          input
            {|
              l := ContinueWith idesc l;
              input := im;
              destination := s';
              output := om
            |};
        destination :=
          equivocator_state_zero
            (destination
               {|
                 l := ContinueWith idesc l;
                 input := im;
                 destination := s';
                 output := om
               |});
        output :=
          output
            {|
              l := ContinueWith idesc l;
              input := im;
              destination := s';
              output := om
            |}
      |}
end

        l := l0;

              output := om

               {|

                 input := im;
                 destination := s';
                 output := om
               |});

              input := im;
              destination := s';

  := equivocator_oracle_dec (has_been_received X) _.

Section ComputableSentMessages_lifting.

Lifting the ComputableSentMessages property

Context
  {Hsent_messages : ComputableSentMessages X}
  `(EqDecision message)
  (Hbeen_sent_X := @ComputableSentMessages_HasBeenSentCapability message X Hsent_messages)
  .

Existing Instance Hbeen_sent_X.
We define the sent_messages_fn for the equivocator_vlsm as the union of all sent_messages_fn for its internal machines. 
Definition equivocator_sent_messages_fn
  (s : vstate equivocator_vlsm)
  : set message
  :=
  fold_right set_union []
    (map
      (fun i =>
        match equivocator_state_project s i with
        | None => []
        | Some si => sent_messages_fn X si
        end)
      (up_to_n_listing (equivocator_state_n s))).
equivocator_sent_messages_fn captures all sent_messages for that state.

Finally, we define the ComputableSentMessages instance for the equivocator_vlsm. Note that we can reuse the consistency property proved above since ComputableSentMessages for X implies HasBeenSentCapability. 
Program Definition equivocator_ComputableSentMessages
  : ComputableSentMessages equivocator_vlsm
  :=
  {|
    sent_messages_fn := equivocator_sent_messages_fn;
    sent_messages_full := equivocator_sent_messages_full;
  |}.

  message X Hsent_messages: EqDecision message

‚àÄ s : vstate equivocator_vlsm,
  valid_state_prop
    (pre_loaded_with_all_messages_vlsm
       equivocator_vlsm) s
  ‚Üí ‚àÄ m : message,
      selected_messages_consistency_prop
        equivocator_vlsm (field_selector output) s m
